# User wording does not shorten triggered bot waits

These phrases do **not** waive a triggered wait gate (step 5) or thread closure (step 6) in `git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`:

- "Merge everything" / "batch merge" / "land the queue"
- "Just merge" / "urgency" / frustration tone
- "CI green" / "checks passed" while threads are missing or unsettled
- Skipping the 7-minute wait after creating a new PR or after tagging bots

**Code changes alone do not start a new wait cycle.** Only creating a new PR or tagging bots starts a 7-minute wait. Only an explicit written waiver for that specific PR waives bot closeout for that PR.

